<Author>samimax
<Content>Lovely Hotel, Great Location! We spent four nights in this peaceful, pleasant hotel, just my husband and I for a few days in Paris, without our kids. We had booked a deluxe room but when we arrived at the hotel, we enquired about upgrading to a suite. We were shown a lovely room on the top floor with a living room, large bedroom, and a bathroom with a jacuzzi/bubble bath, which we were offered at a reduced rate and we were keen to accept. The hotel was fairly modern in decor, the beds were comfy and everywhere was nicely cleaned and looked after. Our only criticism would be that the carpets were very dated and quite dirty and the wallpaper needed replacing.Breakfast was good, not the best we've had, but good, a reasonable choice and kept us going throughout the day. Patrick, the hotel concierge, was extremely helpful and went out of his way to chat to us and give us any information we needed. The location was good. We walked to the arc de triomphe easily and caught a sightseeing bus from nearby, which we used for two days to get around Paris. This was a very pleasant hotel and we would stay there again. 
