<Author>Janbo53
<Content>An unexpected surprise We booked to stay in the Residence Foch for our weekend in Paris, after much research and taking the advice from the Tripadvisor reviews. The day before we were due to go, the hotel contacted us and because of problems with the water there, they had rebooked us to stay at La Villa Maillot. I was a bit disappointed, especially because Residence Foch was number 1 on the popularity index, and the Villa Maillot was number 364! However, we had a very good experience there. The rooms and the bed were a very generous size for a Paris hotel, there was a good sized very pleasant bathroom, bath robes etc etc. The helpful hotel staff recommended an absolutely excellent restaurant nearby (L'Auberge Dab)It is 10 mins from the Champs Elysee, 2 mins from a metro station, so in a good position to get to wherever you are going.If you want a good comfortable hotel, this is great, but the downside it that it is clearly a business hotel and is quite impersonal and doesn't have that Parisienne je ne sais quoi.... but having said that, we had a great couple of days there. 
