<Author>lanzarotelover
<Content>A touch of luxury We stayed at this hotel with our 11 year old son, who shared our room. If I have one negative comment about this hotel it would be that the room we were in was just a bit too small to accommodate a third bed. However, the room was otherwise great. It was really thickly carpeted and we heard no noise from other rooms which is really unusual. There was a plasma screen TV on the wall and a mini bar which we used to chill our own drinks! The bathroom was lovely - marble, great shower, loads of hot water for a deep bath, hairdryer, toiletries and towels changed twice a day. Toilet and bidet were screened off from the rest of the bathroom by a sliding door. There is a turndown service at night and they leave you a little card with the next day's weather forecast. The room had air-conditioning/heating which was great because it was freezing when we were there (October).Breakfast was buffet service, although if you weren't early, there sometimes wasn't much choice left. If you were lucky though, there was cereal, salmon, scrambled eggs, cold meats and cheeses, fruit and, best of all, pastries and croissants! The coffee is excellent and strong and our son loved the hot chocolate. They also happily do refills. The breakfast room is lovely - it's quite small with a glass covered roof and it looks onto a small garden. In fact the whole hotel is really beautifully presented and very clean. The decor throughout is modern and tasteful. We found all the staff really friendly although I don't know if it helped that I speak reasonable French. The whole atmosphere is very welcoming and cosy. It felt like a nice hotel the minute you stepped through the doors.Location wise, it's on a nice quiet street, near a Metro station and within walking distance of the Arc de Triomphe. There is a small supermarket across the road and an excellent Chinese restaurant next door which served the best tofu I've ever had anywhere.If you're going to Paris for any reason, this hotel is worth considering. We would definitely stay there again - we loved it! 
<Date>Sep 8, 2005
